Dynamics.content:
Newton’s Laws of Motion

Object in motion stays in motion unless acted upon by an external force. Inertia.
F = ma
Every action has an equal and opposite reaction. F_{AB} = - F_{BA}

Forces
A push or a pull, vector quantities measured in Newtons (N). The F_{net} is the sum of all forces.
Friction
Kinetic friction: Friction that object feels when moving, where F_{fr} = \mu_{k}F_{N}
For objects at rest, there is static friction, where F_{fr} &lt; \mu_{s}F_{N} .
Note: \mu_{s} &gt; \mu_{k}

