Proof-of-One-Dimensional-Collision.content:
Start with momentum
m_{1}v_{1} + m_{2}v_{2} = m_{1}v_{1}^{&#039;} + m_{2}v_{2}^{&#039;}
Do the same for kinetic energy
\frac{1}{2}m_{1}v_{1}^2 + \frac{1}{2}m_{2}v_{2}^2 = \frac{1}{2}m_{1}v_{1}^{&#039;2} + \frac{1}{2}m_{1}v_{2}^{&#039;2}
Eliminate the constants by factoring them out from both equations. Then, rearrange to set up for elimination by using difference of squares.
